microstructure: dendritic structure after etching, transforms to polycrystalline structure after homogenization
evidence: As-cast NbZrTi alloy is composed of two disordered bcc phases with similar lattice parameters, and as-cast NbHfZrTi alloy forms a single disordered bcc phase. These two alloys are composed of a single bcc phase after homogenization at 1373 K for 10 h. As-cast NbZrTi and NbHfZrTi alloys have excellent compressive properties and exhibit significant work-hardening effect at room temperature.
